For backward binary compatibility with OS X v10.3 and earlier, the default implementation of this method invokes
if it is overridden. When doing this it uses private functionality to arrange for the print settings to take effect (despite the fact that the override of

can’t possibly know about them) and to get notified when the print operation has been completed, so it can message the delegate at the correct time. Correct messaging of the delegate is necessary for correct handling of the Print Apple event.

abstract.text: Construct and manage a graphical, event-driven user interface for your macOS app.
An abstract class that defines the interface for macOS documents.

Exports a PDF representation of the document’s current contents.
